#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:1
msgid "Black Docker image"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:3
msgid ""
"Official _Black_ Docker images are available on [Docker Hub](https://hub."
"docker.com/r/pyfound/black)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:6
msgid "_Black_ images with the following tags are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:8
msgid ""
"release numbers, e.g. `21.5b2`, `21.6b0`, `21.7b0` etc. ℹ Recommended for "
"users who want to use a particular version of _Black_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:0
msgid "<br />\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:0
msgid "\\\\\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:10
msgid ""
"`latest_release` - tag created when a new version of _Black_ is released. ℹ "
"Recommended for users who want to use released versions of _Black_. It maps "
"to [the latest release](https://github.com/psf/black/releases/latest) of "
"_Black_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:13
msgid ""
"`latest_prerelease` - tag created when a new alpha (prerelease) version of "
"_Black_ is released. ℹ Recommended for users who want to preview or test "
"alpha versions of _Black_. Note that the most recent release may be newer "
"than any prerelease, because no prereleases are created before most releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:18
msgid ""
"`latest` - tag used for the newest image of _Black_. ℹ Recommended for users "
"who always want to use the latest version of _Black_, even before it is "
"released."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:22
msgid ""
"There is one more tag used for _Black_ Docker images - `latest_non_release`. "
"It is created for all unreleased [commits on the `main` branch](https://"
"github.com/psf/black/commits/main). This tag is not meant to be used by "
"external users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:27
msgid ""
"From version 23.11.0 the Docker image installs a compiled black into the "
"image."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:29
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:31
msgid ""
"A permanent container doesn't have to be created to use _Black_ as a Docker "
"image. It's enough to run _Black_ commands for the chosen image denoted as `:"
"tag`. In the below examples, the `latest_release` tag is used. If `:tag` is "
"omitted, the `latest` tag will be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:36
msgid ""
"More about _Black_ usage can be found in [Usage and Configuration: The "
"basics](./the_basics.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:39
msgid "Check Black version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:41
msgid "$ docker run --rm pyfound/black:latest_release black --version\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:45
msgid "Check code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:47
msgid ""
"$ docker run --rm --volume $(pwd):/src --workdir /src pyfound/black:"
"latest_release black --check .\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage_and_configuration/black_docker_image.md:51
msgid ""
"_Remark_: besides [regular _Black_ exit codes](./the_basics.md) returned by "
"`--check` option, [Docker exit codes](https://docs.docker.com/engine/"
"reference/run/#exit-status) should also be considered."
msgstr ""
